  "title": "Product Technical Support Engineer (PTS Engineer)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Involvement in vehicle navigation and project commissioning, testing and troubleshooting.</li><li>On-site hardware and software troubleshooting</li><li>Work closely with customer’s engineering team to provide technical consultation and on- and off-site support.</li><li>Advise customers/dealers for all warranty issues</li><li>Conduct technical investigation and ensure prompt closure</li><li>Review the technical challenges and propose suitable technical solutions</li><li>Liaise with factory Central support team to address the product support issues</li><li>Provide technical training to dealers/customers</li><li>Provide technical training to internal technical staff</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned by superior.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Education & Experience</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Electrical/Degree in Mechanical/Degree in Mechatronic or Diploma in Engineering field with 10 years of working experienced </li></ul><p><strong>Skills & Competencies</strong></p><ul><li>At least 5 years of experience in hands on experience of container handling equipment (eg. Rubber tyred gantry, Quay cranes, Straddle carriers, Container handlers, forklifts and terminal\ntractors)</li></ul><ul><li>Good knowledge in high voltage, engines, transmissions, hydraulics systems and electrical  systems</li></ul><ul><li>Background in Control Systems and/or Mechatronics is a plus</li></ul><ul><li>Team player</li></ul><ul><li>Possess great problem solving skills</li></ul><ul><li>Has excellent interpersonal and communication skills</li></ul><ul><li>Must be independent and possess initiative </li></ul><ul><li>Work closely with internal stakeholders and provide necessary technical support</li></ul><ul><li>Travelling is required</li></ul><p><br />Chan Chee Meng<br />EA 07C3069<br />R1110620</p>",
